  "contentHtml": "\n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p><a href=\"/tag/indore\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Indore</a>: <a href=\"/tag/ankura+hospitals\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Ankura Hospitals</a> for women and children has expanded its presence in Central India with the launch of its 120-bed super speciality hospital in Vijay Nagar, Indore.The hospital chain said this marks its strategic entry into Madhya Pradesh, as it looks to  further strengthen its presence across Western and Central India.The newly launched hospital offers specialised services in obstetrics &amp; gynaecology, <a href=\"/tag/high-risk+pregnancy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">high-risk pregnancy</a> management, neonatology, level III Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU), paediatrics, paediatric surgery, Paediatric Intensive Care Unit (PICU), foetal medicine, fertility &amp; IVF, gynaecological care and 24x7 emergency services, it added.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>Ankura Hospitals currently operates over 1,500 beds in 17 centers across Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, Maharashtra and Odisha.The healthcare network said with its 18th centre in Indore it aims to address the growing demand for specialised maternal and child healthcare in the region.“While Indore has emerged as an important healthcare destination, many families still travel outside the state for the management of high-risk pregnancies, premature newborns, congenital disorders and complex paediatric conditions. The new facility aims to bridge this gap by providing comprehensive tertiary care closer to home,” the hospital added.                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                                                            <!-- <li>By <span>Online Bureau</span>,</li> -->\n                                    \n\n                                                                            <li>By\n                                                                                            <a>Online Bureau</a>\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                        , \n                                                                                    </li>\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/88675629/ETHealthWorld\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ETHealthWorld</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On Jul 17, 2026 at 04:16 PM IST</li> -->\n                                    <li>Published On Jul 17, 2026 at 04:16 PM IST</li>\n                                    <!-- <li class=\"desktop-view\">1 min read</li> -->\n                                </ul>\n                            \n                                        \n\n                    \n\n                    <!-- Comment Section -->\n                                            \n                                        <!-- Comment Section -->\n\n                    \n                      \n    \n            <p>\n                </p><h2>Join the community of 2M+ industry professionals. </h2>   \n                <h3>Subscribe to 